<!-- COSMOS SPECIAL FEATURES - INDUSTRIAL MINING -->
<section class="relative max-w-[1200px] mx-auto px-5 py-20 flex flex-col gap-16">

  <!-- Header -->
  <div class="text-center md:text-left mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">
      What Makes Cosmos Coatings Essential for Mining
    </h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 md:text-lg leading-relaxed max-w-[700px]">
      Cosmos Coatings are engineered for the extreme conditions of mining operations. Our high-performance epoxy coatings provide **abrasion resistance, chemical protection, and thermal stability**, keeping equipment running safely and efficiently.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- Feature Cards -->
  <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">

    <!-- Card 1: Abrasion Resistance -->
    <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-xl p-8 border-l-4 border-[#E77B00] shadow-md hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow duration-300 flex flex-col gap-5">
      <div class="w-12 h-12 flex items-center justify-center bg-[#E77B00]/10 text-[#E77B00] rounded-full text-2xl font-semibold">
        🪨
      </div>
      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[#E77B00]">Extreme Abrasion Resistance</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
        Formulated with **ceramic-filled epoxy resins** to resist wear from abrasive ores, slurries, and heavy particulate flow in tanks, chutes, and conveyors.
      </p>
      <span class="text-sm text-gray-500 italic">
        Example: Slurry chutes coated with Cosmos last 3x longer than standard coatings.
      </span>
    </div>

    <!-- Card 2: Chemical & Corrosion Protection -->
    <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-xl p-8 border-l-4 border-[#E77B00] shadow-md hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow duration-300 flex flex-col gap-5">
      <div class="w-12 h-12 flex items-center justify-center bg-[#E77B00]/10 text-[#E77B00] rounded-full text-2xl font-semibold">
        🧪
      </div>
      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[#E77B00]">Chemical & Corrosion Protection</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
        Incorporates **corrosion inhibitors** and acid-resistant epoxy resins to protect tanks, pipelines, and steel structures from sulfuric acid, copper leach solutions, and industrial chemicals.
      </p>
      <span class="text-sm text-gray-500 italic">
        Example: Copper and nickel plant pipelines remain corrosion-free for years.
      </span>
    </div>

    <!-- Card 3: Thermal & Moisture Stability -->
    <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-xl p-8 border-l-4 border-[#E77B00] shadow-md hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow duration-300 flex flex-col gap-5">
      <div class="w-12 h-12 flex items-center justify-center bg-[#E77B00]/10 text-[#E77B00] rounded-full text-2xl font-semibold">
        🔥
      </div>
      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[#E77B00]">Thermal & Moisture Stability</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
        High-solid epoxy resins maintain adhesion and mechanical properties in **extreme temperatures and humid mining environments**.
      </p>
      <span class="text-sm text-gray-500 italic">
        Example: Conveyor housings coated with Cosmos remain fully protected at 60°C and high humidity.
      </span>
    </div>

  </div>

</section>
